 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# RPFR-GUI Quick Start\n",
    "\n",
    "Load the QM9 dataset and resolve molecule identifiers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "cell-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Libraries loaded OK\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "project_root = Path.cwd().parent.parent\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(project_root / 'src'))\n",
    "\n",
    "from rpfr_gui.data import ChemistryResolver, H5Provider\n",
    "\n",
    "H5_PATH  = Path('/Users/simonandren/QM9_H5/qm9s.h5')\n",
    "IDX_PATH = project_root / 'data/processed/index.parquet'\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Libraries loaded OK')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Generate or Load the Index\n",
    "\n",
    "The index maps canonical SMILES to molecule IDs in the HDF5 file. This only needs to be built once."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "cell-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Index already exists at /Users/simonandren/Documents/isotope-informed-crn/data/processed/index.parquet\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "IDX_PATH.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "if not IDX_PATH.exists():\n",
    "    print('Building index... (this may take a few minutes)')\n",
    "    ChemistryResolver.build_index(\n",
    "        h5_path=H5_PATH,\n",
    "        output_path=IDX_PATH,\n",
    "        smiles_dataset='SMILES',\n",
    "    )\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f'Index already exists at {IDX_PATH}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Resolve Molecule IDs\n",
    "\n",
    "The `ChemistryResolver` canonicalizes SMILES via RDKit and looks up the corresponding HDF5 group key."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "cell-6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Methane (C) -> 000001\n",
      "  C          -> 000001\n",
      "  CC         -> 000007\n",
      "  CCO        -> 000014\n",
      "  CO         -> 000008\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "resolver = ChemistryResolver(IDX_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Single resolve\n",
    "methane_id = resolver.resolve('C', id_type='smiles')\n",
    "print(f'Methane (C) -> {methane_id}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Batch resolve\n",
    "molecules = ['C', 'CC', 'CCO', 'CO']\n",
    "mol_ids = resolver.batch_resolve(molecules, id_type='smiles')\n",
    "\n",
    "for smiles, mol_id in mol_ids.items():\n",
    "    print(f'  {smiles:10s} -> {mol_id}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Load RPFR Data\n",
    "\n",
    "`H5Provider` lazily reads per-atom RPFR values from the HDF5 file.\n",
    "\n",
    "Available temperatures: 20, 60, 100, 140, 180, 220, 260, 273, 298, 300, 340, 380, 420 K"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "id": "cell-8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Methane RPFR at 300 K:\n",
      "   Atom_Index Atom_Symbol  RPFR_300K\n",
      "0           0           C   1.117726\n",
      "1           1           H  11.227987\n",
      "2           2           H  11.228070\n",
      "3           3           H  11.228245\n",
      "4           4           H  11.228226\n",
      "\n",
      "SMILES: C\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "provider = H5Provider(H5_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Methane at 300 K\n",
    "rpfr = provider.get_rpfr(methane_id, temperature=300.0)\n",
    "print('Methane RPFR at 300 K:')\n",
    "print(rpfr)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nSMILES: {provider.get_structure(methane_id)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "id": "cell-9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ethanol RPFR at 273 K:\n",
      "   Atom_Index Atom_Symbol  RPFR_273K\n",
      "0           0           C   1.160638\n",
      "1           1           C   1.178425\n",
      "2           2           O   1.105912\n",
      "3           3           H  16.920590\n",
      "4           4           H  16.922174\n",
      "5           5           H  16.587541\n",
      "6           6           H  19.155349\n",
      "7           7           H  19.154573\n",
      "8           8           H  20.164396\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Ethanol at 273 K\n",
    "ethanol_id = mol_ids['CCO']\n",
    "rpfr_ethanol = provider.get_rpfr(ethanol_id, temperature=273.0)\n",
    "print('Ethanol RPFR at 273 K:')\n",
    "print(rpfr_ethanol)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Next Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "- **`01_data_exploration.ipynb`** — Visualize per-atom RPFR values in 3D\n",
    "- **`02_rpfr_3d_visualization.ipynb`** — Interactive temperature and molecule widgets"
   ]
  }
